    <h1>Health-Cost Navigator</h1>
    <p><strong>Group Project</strong> | Feb 2025 â€“ May 2025 | University of Texas at Dallas</p>
  </header>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Project Overview</h2>
    <p>
      Health-Cost Navigator is a comprehensive data engineering and analytics initiative aimed at improving U.S. healthcare price transparency.
      The project focused on collecting, transforming, and visualizing hospital price data across Charlotte, Chicago, and Las Vegas.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Key Contributions</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Processed over <strong>10 million records</strong> using an end-to-end ETL pipeline.</li>
      <li>Parsed and cleaned JSON data to structured CSV and transformed wide-format data to long-format for modeling.</li>
      <li>Leveraged <strong>Snowflake</strong> for cloud-based data warehousing and transformations.</li>
      <li>Developed a <strong>Streamlit dashboard</strong> for interactive analysis by hospital, treatment, CPT code, and payer.</li>
      <li>Enabled comparative pricing insights and hospital benchmarking across metro regions.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
    <p>Python, Snowflake, MongoDB, Streamlit, SQL, Excel, JSON</p>
  </div>

